-- Ukraine May Set Duty on Chemical, Metal Exports, Kommersant Says
-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 2012-02-08T08:08:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/ukraine-may-set-duty-on-chemical-metal-exports-kommersant-says.html
Ukraine may introduce a 1.5 percent
duty on chemical and metal exports,  Kommersant-Ukraine  newspaper
reported, citing a draft law registered in the parliament.  The revenue from the export tax will be used for “social
needs,” the newspaper said. The draft law was registered by
Hryhoriy Smityukh, a member of President  Viktor Yanukovych ’s
party, according to Kommersant.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
 dkrasnolutsk@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  